Package: unforcedChoice
Type: Package
Title: Signal Detection Models of Unforced Choice
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Victor H Cervantes
Maintainer: Victor H Cervantes <victorhc@illinois.net>
Description: 
    Signal Detection Models of Unforced Choice. Includes functions to compute predictions and to fit standard models of unforced choice
    (aka Independent Observations Model, Watson et al., 1973, <doi:10.1037/h0034736>),
    the Integration Model (Graham et al., 1987, <doi:10.1016/0022-2496(87)90021-6>), 
    the Ensemble Model (Wixted et al., 2018, <doi:10.1016/j.cogpsych.2018.06.001>),
    and the Dependent Observations Model (Akan et al., 2021, <doi:10.1037/xap0000340>). 
    Additional models may be easily specified with a coefficients matrix (see examples).
Imports: mvtnorm, ggplot2, rlang, dplyr, magrittr, tidyr, tidyselect
License: GPL (>= 2)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.2.1
